<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="317" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1578,1999]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1578,1603]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This species can be distinguished from all other Neotropical 
<taxonomicName box="[1006,1118,1578,1603]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Epirhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1006,1118,1578,1603]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="317">Epirhyssa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following characters: 
<number box="[396,408,1615,1639]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" value="1.0">1</number>
) fore wing with two blackish bands; 
<number box="[831,846,1615,1639]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" value="2.0">2</number>
) apex of hind wing yellowish; 
<number box="[1198,1212,1615,1639]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" value="3.0">3</number>
) pronotum and mid coxa generally blackish; and 
<number box="[478,493,1651,1675]" pageId="6" pageNumber="317" value="4.0">4</number>
) hind coxa totally black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
